This project builds on and redistributes patches for the following
third-party works. Their own licenses govern their respective code.

1. huggingface/speech-to-speech
   https://github.com/huggingface/speech-to-speech
   License: Apache License 2.0
   Not vendored here — `setup.sh` clones and pins it at a specific commit.
   `patches/` contains an overlay pack of modified files from this framework
   (see patches/README.md for exactly which files and why).

2. met4citizen/TalkingHead
   https://github.com/met4citizen/TalkingHead
   License: MIT
   The webclient's avatar rendering code under `webclient/avatar/vendor/`
   integrates with this library.

3. Bundled avatar heads (webclient/avatar/model/*.glb)
   Six ready heads are redistributed from the met4citizen/TalkingHead
   repository, mirroring its own public distribution. They are NOT uniformly
   licensed — see webclient/avatar/model/LICENSE-NOTE.txt for the per-file
   terms (mpfb.glb is CC0/public domain; the others are non-commercial /
   personal-use assets created with Ready Player Me, AvatarSDK, Avaturn, and
   VRoid Studio). For any non-personal use, replace them with heads you have
   rights to.

4. Vendored libraries (webclient/avatar/vendor/)
   - three.js (MIT) — 3D rendering.
   - met4citizen/TalkingHead modules (MIT) — 3D head render + lip-sync glue,
     with two small local patches noted inline (meshopt decoder wiring and
     the upstream armature-root fallback).
   - HeadAudio by Mika Suominen (MIT, see its LICENSE) — real-time
     audio-driven viseme detection (webclient/avatar/vendor/headaudio/).

5. Fonts (webclient/themes/fonts/)
   Cinzel — SIL Open Font License (see OFL.txt alongside the font files).

Theme reference images and the 2D still-avatar source image used during
development are NOT redistributed (see .gitignore) — supply your own image
for the 2D avatar path. Nothing in this NOTICE grants rights to any asset
not present in the repository.

